Package <Unnamed>

Interface Summary
Interface  
 

Class Summary
BookingInformation A class to maintain the information of each booking.
BookingRepository A class to maintain an arbitrary number of booking informations.
BookingStatus A class to maintain the booking status for day.
Cinema A class to hold the information of the Cinema.
CinemaRepository A class to maintain an arbitrary number of cinemas.
CinemaSystem Provides the interfaces of a simple Cinema Seats Booking System.
CinemaSystemEngine Provides the engine of a simple Cinema Seats Booking System.
Command This class holds information about a command issued by the user.
CommandLineInterface Provides a command line interface to the Cinema Booking System.
CommandWords This class holds an enumeration of all command words known to the Cinema Booking System.
DayParameters A class to recognise Days as they are typed in.
DialogBox Provides a class used for GUI of the Cinema Booking System.
FileHandler Provides the file-handling operations on an CinemaSystemEngine.
FilmShow A class to hold the information of a single filmshow A film show has three attributes: The name of the film, The name of the cinema, The name of the day.
FilmShowRepository A class to maintain an arbitrary number of film shows.
GraphicalInterface Provides the GUI of the Cinema Booking System.
Parser This parser reads user input and tries to interpret it as a valid command.
Row A class to maintain a row of seats in a cinema hall.
Seat A class to maintain the information of each seat in a Cinema Hall.
Theatre A class to maintain the information of a theatre.
UserParameters A class to recognise Users as they are typed in.
 

Enum Summary
CommandWord Representations for all the valid command words in the Cinema Booking System along with their number of parameters.
Day Enumeration class Day Representations for all the days of a week
User Enumeration class User Representations for all users.
 

Exception Summary
InvalidCommandException Captures an input that is not considered as a valid command of the system against the legal mode to execute.
UnrecognizedCommandException Captures an input that is not recognized as any valid command for the system.
